            . My Master is a Smith, he did work for Mr. Colebrant the <rs id="t17320223-14-viclabel82" type="occupation">Sugar-Baker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17320223-14-victim113 t17320223-14-viclabel82"></join>, and so I became acquainted with the Prisoner, who is Mr. Colebrant's <rs id="t17320223-14-deflabel83" type="occupation">Coachman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17320223-14-defend111 t17320223-14-deflabel83"></join>. The Butter was in a Warehouse over Mr. Colebrant's Stables; the Prisoner took it from thence, and deliver'd it to me to sell for him, which I did for 9 s. a Firkin to several Tallow-Chandlers; I sold 8 Firkins to Carter (he that sells Candles so cheap) at the Half-Moon in Spittle-Fields; 3 Firkins to the Tallow-Chandler, at the Crown over-against Carter's, and 4 to 
               <persName id="t17320223-14-person117">
                  Thomas 
                  Rivet 
               <interp inst="t17320223-14-person117" type="surname" value="Rivet"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17320223-14-person117" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
